  Apache-2.0 code from pipelock is confined to files named for their origin.
  These files, and only these files, contain vendored upstream work:

    normalize/pipelock.go        <- internal/normalize/normalize.go
    normalize/pipelock_test.go   <- internal/normalize/normalize_test.go
    detect/rules_pipelock.go     <- internal/config/defaults.go
                                    internal/scanner/core.go (one pattern)

  Every other file in this repository is airlock's own work. In particular
  detect/rules_seed.go -- which assigns a severity and category to each vendored
  pattern -- is airlock's editorial judgment, not upstream data: pipelock's
  pattern struct carries no severity field at all.

  Modifications, per Apache-2.0 section 4(b), are enumerated in each vendored
  file's header. In summary:

    normalize/pipelock.go       ForDLP removed (out of scope). StripCombiningMarks
                                renamed and unexported; airlock's corrected version,
                                which recomposes with NFC, lives in normalize.go.
    normalize/pipelock_test.go  ForDLP tests removed. Benchmarks rewritten off
                                testing.Loop to hold the go 1.22 language floor.
    detect/rules_pipelock.go    Regexes extracted verbatim. Three credential-exfil
                                patterns not taken (egress/DLP, out of scope).

Nothing in this product is derived from pipelock's enterprise/ tree, which is
licensed under the Elastic License 2.0 rather than Apache-2.0.

